3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates funding rates hourly based on the premium between perpetual and spot prices, with payments occurring every hour at the top of each hour. The on-chain order book ensures transparent price discovery without relying on external oracles for funding calculations. Funding rates are determined by the 1-hour TWAP of the premium, creating more frequent arbitrage opportunities compared to traditional 8-hour cycles."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","AVAX","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"AVAX/USDT on Hyperliquid benefits from significant trading volume in the L1 token category, often generating substantial funding rate premiums during market volatility. The hourly funding cycles provide 8x more opportunities per day compared to traditional exchanges, making it attractive for active arbitrage strategies."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"AVAX/USDT funding rates on Hyperliquid typically range from -0.05% to 0.15% per hour during normal market conditions. During major Avalanche ecosystem announcements or subnet launches, funding rates can spike above 0.3% hourly as leveraged long positions accumulate. The 1-hour intervals create more granular rate movements compared to 8-hour cycles, with rates often mean-reverting faster due to arbitrage activity. Weekend periods generally show lower funding volatility as institutional activity decreases."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategies"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The hourly funding schedule creates 192 potential arbitrage opportunities per month, significantly more than traditional exchanges. Cross-exchange arbitrage between Hyperliquid and CEXes like Binance or Bybit becomes profitable when rate differentials exceed 0.02-0.03% after accounting for transaction costs. Delta-neutral strategies can capture funding premiums by longing AVAX perpetuals on Hyperliquid while shorting on exchanges with negative rates. The on-chain nature eliminates counterparty risk while USDC settlement reduces stablecoin depeg exposure."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid's single-chain architecture concentrates smart contract risk, though the platform has maintained strong uptime since launch. USDC-only settlement eliminates USDT depeg risk but requires bridging assets from other chains, adding time delays for position adjustments. The newer platform has limited historical data for backtesting strategies compared to established CEXes. Slippage can increase during high volatility periods despite the efficient order book, particularly for larger position sizes exceeding $100K notional."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are AVAX/USDT funding rates calculated on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Funding rates are calculated and paid every hour on the hour. This creates 24 funding events per day, providing more frequent arbitrage opportunities compared to the standard 8-hour cycles used by most centralized exchanges."},{"question":"What are typical AVAX/USDT funding rates on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Normal funding rates range from -0.05% to 0.15% per hour. During high volatility or major AVAX ecosystem events, rates can exceed 0.3% hourly as directional positioning increases among traders."},{"question":"Can I arbitrage AVAX funding rates between Hyperliquid and other exchanges?","answer":"Yes, cross-exchange arbitrage is possible by comparing Hyperliquid's hourly rates with 8-hour rates on CEXes. Profitable opportunities typically arise when rate differentials exceed 0.02-0.03% after accounting for trading fees and potential slippage."},{"question":"What are the main risks of trading AVAX perpetuals on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Primary risks include smart contract risk from the newer platform, single-chain dependency, and USDC-only settlement requiring cross-chain bridging. The on-chain nature eliminates traditional counterparty risk but introduces blockchain-specific considerations."}]}]
